cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

The paper deals with video understanding and proposes a learning-based approach for multi-layered video representation. This involves novel uncertainty-capturing 3D convolutional architectures and training them to separate blended videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper deals with separating reflections and factoring out shadows, which involves some level of reasoning and decision-making, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category. The paper also involves multimedia processing, which makes cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with realistic scenes, which may involve some level of graphics, making cs.GR (Graphics) another possible category.
